1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a method for mapping 3D carotid surfaces to a standardized 2D carotid template, which involves image processing and analysis techniques commonly used in computer vision.
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with the visualization and flattening of 3D carotid surfaces, which is a common topic in graphics research.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of density-equalizing maps and reference maps, which are concepts related to information theory and data compression.
4. cs.MS (Mathematical Software) - The paper proposes a novel algorithm for flattening 3D carotid surfaces, which involves mathematical computations and may be of interest to researchers in mathematical software.
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves the use of numerical methods for mapping 3D carotid surfaces to a 2D template, which is a topic of interest in numerical analysis.
